    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Memphis</placeName>
                <date>July 1 1860</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Rev Sir!</p>
            <p>It is long that I have <del>not</del> received any lines from you.<lb/> I suppose you
                are very busy, especially <del>that</del> as the day<lb/> draws near when the <hi
                    rend="underline">board of delegates</hi> will reassemble.<lb/> I wish, I could
                be present, but business etc with-<lb/>holds me of enjoying the sight of men who
                still act in<lb/> behalf of that time honored Judaism. I wonder sir!<lb/> how it was
                and still is possible, that you could<lb/>; fight our battles so long without
                retreating a single moment,<lb/> after having been so often insulted by those <hi
                    rend="underline">renegades</hi><lb/> and so little supported by those for whom
                you appeared<lb/> as champion. Is there no hope that you and the<lb/> cause you
                represent will triumph? I wish I<lb/> had the power to write with such facility as
                you have.<lb/> I would assist you with all my might. Dear Sir<lb/> if there will not
                be made a decisive step, those<lb/> infidels will promulgate their nefarious
                doctrines, the<lb/> people will swallow the gilded pill offered to them<lb/> by the
                pseudo-doctors. I have tried and will<lb/> still try to keep them out of our
                regions, though<lb/> they have triumphed for a while. <persName>Wise</persName> is
                trying to<lb/> get one of his emissaries here, and I believe he<lb/> will succeed
                for the infidels stand on the lead<lb/> now. I will write you all about it
                after<lb/> a while. If you find it worthy of appearing<lb/> in your valuable paper,
                insert the <sic>the</sic> following few<lb/> words—Why <hi rend="underline">do we
                    hide</hi> it?</p>
        </body>
